# TDD RED Phase: Worker Loader Integration

Write failing tests for Worker Loader sandbox execution.

## Test Cases to Write

### Worker Creation
```typescript
describe('createWorkerEvaluator', () => {
  it('should create worker with Worker Loader', async () => {
    const mockLoader = createMockLoader();
    const evaluator = createWorkerEvaluator(mockLoader, mockDbAccess, 'return 42');

    expect(evaluator).toBeDefined();
    expect(evaluator.execute).toBeInstanceOf(Function);
  });

  it('should configure compatibility date', async () => {
    const mockLoader = createMockLoader();
    createWorkerEvaluator(mockLoader, mockDbAccess, 'return 1');

    expect(mockLoader.get).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
      expect.any(String),
      expect.any(Function)
    );

    const config = await mockLoader.getLastConfig();
    expect(config.compatibilityDate).toBe('2025-06-01');
  });

  it('should set globalOutbound to null for network isolation', async () => {
    const mockLoader = createMockLoader();
    createWorkerEvaluator(mockLoader, mockDbAccess, 'fetch("http://evil.com")');

    const config = await mockLoader.getLastConfig();
    expect(config.globalOutbound).toBeNull();
  });

  it('should include DB_PROXY binding', async () => {
    const mockLoader = createMockLoader();
    createWorkerEvaluator(mockLoader, mockDbAccess, 'return 1');

    const config = await mockLoader.getLastConfig();
    expect(config.env.DB_PROXY).toBeDefined();
  });
});
```

