# TDD Refactor Phase: CDC Optimization

## Refactoring Goals

### 1. Efficient Batching
- Configurable batch size (default: 1000 events)
- Time-based flush (default: 5 seconds)
- Memory-bounded buffer
- Backpressure handling

### 2. Parquet Serialization
- Convert CDC events to Parquet format
- Optimize for columnar storage
- Support schema evolution
- Compression (snappy/zstd)

### 3. Direct R2 Fallback
- When Pipelines unavailable, write to R2 directly
- Parquet files with Hive partitioning
- Compatible with S3Queue consumption

## Code Changes
```typescript
// Enhanced buffer with Parquet output
class CDCBuffer {
  private events: CDCEvent[] = [];

  async flush(): Promise<void> {
    if (this.pipeline) {
      await this.pipeline.send(this.events);
    } else {
      const parquet = await this.toParquet(this.events);
      await this.r2.put(this.getPartitionedKey(), parquet);
    }
  }

  private async toParquet(events: CDCEvent[]): Promise<ArrayBuffer>;
}
```

